    <stitle>MULTI-LINK FRONT AIR SUSPENSION - DESCRIPTION</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>DESCRIPTION</title>
        <svcsubsecinfo>
            <para>The multi-link front air suspension is the ultimate in smooth, shock and vibration-free ride with a
                preset constant frame height.
            </para>
            <para>The multi-link front air suspension adjusts to load changes automatically, providing a "low rate"
                suspension with a light or no load condition, and a "higher rate" suspension with heavier loads. The
                major components of the multi-link front air suspension system are as follows.
            </para>
            <figure id="f0301501" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg03/g0301501.webp" type="webp" scalefitwidth="312px" scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 1. Multi-link Front Air Suspension System</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. HEIGHT CONTROL VALVE</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. SHOCK</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. AIR SPRING</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. TOP TORQUE ROD</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. SWAY BAR</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. SWAY BAR CLAMPS</callout1>
                    <callout1>7. BOTTOM TORQUE ROD</callout1>
                    <callout1>8. TRANSVERSE TORQUE ROD</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcsubsecinfo>
    </svcsubsec>
